Evendri Makhana Exports 🍿
Premium D2C Fox Nuts E-commerce Experience

A high-fidelity, responsive e-commerce web application built with a focus on modern UI/UX, state persistence, and seamless data flow. Evendri Makhana provides purely roasted, organic gourmet snacks directly to customers.

🚀 Technical Highlights
1. Persistent State Management
Unlike many front-end projects, Evendri uses a centralized CartManager logic. By utilizing LocalStorage, the user's shopping bag remains synchronized across the home page and individual product detail pages, ensuring no data loss during navigation.

2. Dynamic Routing & Parameterized UI
The project uses URLSearchParams to handle dynamic content.

Product Details: product.html?id=1 fetches and renders data dynamically from a centralized JavaScript object.

Express Checkout: The "Buy Now" feature uses custom URL parameters (?buyNowPrice=XXX) to bypass the cart and trigger a single-product payment modal.

3. Real-time DOM Rendering
The cart drawer implements a "reactive" approach. Every time an item is added or a quantity is adjusted, the script recalculates the subtotal and re-renders the HTML structure in real-time without a page refresh.

4. API Integration (EmailJS)
The contact section is fully functional. It integrates with EmailJS to capture user inquiries and deliver them directly to the business inbox, featuring a custom loading spinner for enhanced UX.

